      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-03-20T15:47:57Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Addiction Treatment Access Improvement Act of 2018</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Controlled Substances Act to revise the qualifications required for a practitioner to administer, dispense, or prescribe narcotic drugs for maintenance or detoxification treatment in an office-based opioid treatment program.</p> <p>It increases the maximum patient limit for a qualifying practitioner who meets certain requirements. The maximum patient limit is the maximum number of patients a qualifying practitioner can treat at one time.</p> <p>The bill expands qualifying practitioners to include additional nonphysician practitioners: clinical nurse specialists, certified registered nurse anesthetists, and certified nurse midwives.</p> <p>It makes permanent the authorization for certain nonphysician practitioners to become qualifying practitioners.</p>]]></text>
